U||   Divine Volition. With the view of producing impediment, the organic
U||   life and matter, (complex, substantial, and law-encumbered,) were
U||   contrived.
U||   P. But again—why need this impediment have been produced?
U||   V. The result of law inviolate is perfection—right—negative happiness.
U||   The result of law violate is imperfection, wrong, positive pain.
U||   Through the impediments afforded by the number, complexity, and
U||   substantiality of the laws of organic life and matter, the violation of
