U||   have thought thus,) as on account of the pertinacity with which he
U||   maintained it. This opinion, in its general form, was that of the
U||   sentience of all vegetable things. But, in his disordered fancy, the
U||   idea had assumed a more daring character, and trespassed, under certain
U||   conditions, upon the kingdom of inorganization. I lack words to express
U||   the full extent, or the earnest abandon of his persuasion. The belief,
U||   however, was connected (as I have previously hinted) with the gray
U||   stones of the home of his forefathers. The conditions of the sentience
