U||   Its evidence—the evidence of the sentience—was to be seen, he said,
U||   (and I here started as he spoke,) in the gradual yet certain
U||   condensation of an atmosphere of their own about the waters and the
U||   walls. The result was discoverable, he added, in that silent, yet
U||   importunate and terrible influence which for centuries had moulded the
U||   destinies of his family, and which made him what I now saw him—what he
U||   was. Such opinions need no comment, and I will make none.
