U||   About midway in the short vista which my dreamy vision took in, one
U||   small circular island, profusely verdured, reposed upon the bosom of
U||   the stream.
U||   So blended bank and shadow there
U||   That each seemed pendulous in air—
U||   so mirror-like was the glassy water, that it was scarcely possible to
U||   say at what point upon the slope of the emerald turf its crystal
U||   dominion began.
U||   My position enabled me to include in a single view both the eastern and
U||   western extremities of the islet; and I observed a singularly-marked
U||   difference in their aspects. The latter was all one radiant harem of
U||   garden beauties. It glowed and blushed beneath the eyes of the slant
U||   sunlight, and fairly laughed with flowers. The grass was short,
U||   springy, sweet-scented, and asphodel-interspersed. The trees were
U||   lithe, mirthful, erect—bright, slender, and graceful,—of Eastern figure
