U||   out the heavens, yet every thing had motion through the gentle
U||   sweepings to and fro of innumerable butterflies, that might have been
U||   mistaken for tulips with wings. (*4)
U||   The other or eastern end of the isle was whelmed in the blackest shade.
U||   A sombre, yet beautiful and peaceful gloom here pervaded all things.
U||   The trees were dark in color, and mournful in form and attitude,
