U||   madness of a memory which busies itself among forbidden things.
U||   Very suddenly there came back to my soul motion and sound—the
U||   tumultuous motion of the heart, and, in my ears, the sound of its
U||   beating. Then a pause in which all is blank. Then again sound, and
U||   motion, and touch—a tingling sensation pervading my frame. Then the
