U||   curve to the left, the wall following it as before, while a stream of
U||   considerable volume, diverging from the principal one, makes its way,
U||   with a slight ripple, under the door, and is thus hidden from sight.
U||   The canoe falls into the lesser channel and approaches the gate. Its
U||   ponderous wings are slowly and musically expanded. The boat glides
U||   between them, and commences a rapid descent into a vast amphitheatre
U||   entirely begirt with purple mountains, whose bases are laved by a
U||   gleaming river throughout the full extent of their circuit. Meantime
U||   the whole Paradise of Arnheim bursts upon the view. There is a gush of
U||   entrancing melody; there is an oppressive sense of strange sweet
U||   odor;—there is a dream-like intermingling to the eye of tall slender
U||   Eastern trees—bosky shrubberies—flocks of golden and crimson
U||   birds—lily-fringed lakes—meadows of violets, tulips, poppies,
U||   hyacinths, and tuberoses—long intertangled lines of silver
U||   streamlets—and, upspringing confusedly from amid all, a mass of
U||   semi-Gothic, semi-Saracenic architecture sustaining itself by miracle
U||   in mid-air, glittering in the red sunlight with a hundred oriels,
U||   minarets, and pinnacles; and seeming the phantom handiwork, conjointly,
U||   of the Sylphs, of the Fairies, of the Genii and of the Gnomes.
